Replaced uniform decay with inverse-inertia-weighted decay:

```python
# Before: all edges decay at same rate
w.weight *= (1 - ε)

# After: deep potential wells resist decay, shallow wells decay faster
effective_ε = ε_base · (1 + β) / (1 + β · Φ_norm)  # β = 0.5
```

- Deep Φ (confirmed memory): decays at ~ε × 0.67
- Shallow Φ (noise/stale): decays at ~ε × 1.5
- Result: stale edges clear faster → new regime edges enter top-10 sooner

